# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/).


## [1.0.3] - 2023-07-04

### Changed

- WatneyAstrometry.Core updated to v1.2.3 which introduces improved match 
  filtering. This mainly affects images with large field radiuses and
  massive amounts of stars visible, improving the solve accuracy. 
  Fields with tens of thousands of stars should now solve with better
  accuracy.



## [1.0.2] - 2023-01-21

### Added

- A setting to allow limiting how many threads the solver can use.
  It defaults to CPU logical core count - 1.



## [1.0.1] - 2022-08-23

### Fixed

- Dialogs now open properly at the center of their owner windows.

- The version string is now properly displayed in the main window title
  in Linux.
  
- Latest used paths in file open dialogs are persisted and saved to a 
  config file.



## [1.0.0] - 2022-08-21

### Initial release of Watney Astrometry Desktop

- Release numbering will be independent from WatneyAstrometry.Core
  versioning.
- Additional version build information will be appended to identify
  the build date and source git commit.


